=m><span class=title> Re: DARE admits &quot;possible&quot; flaw in strategy.</span><hr size=1> Marijuana wont make you pawn everything you own and make you repeatedly jab needles in your veins. It wont make you lie on the floor in the fetal position while having seizures and vomiting, hoping for death. So, I personally dont think it should be put in the same class as something like heroin and coke. Marijuana lacks the physical addiction aspect of those other drugs, and is therefore much safer to use. Plus, marijuana isnt likely to make your heart explode or stop your breathing.<br>
<br>
 I have seen a whole lot of people start using coke and heroin thinking they can use it responsibly (what an oxymoron) and only do it every now and then. Not one of them was able to control it like they thought they could. Everyone thinks they are the exception to the rule because I damn sure did. Heh, live and learn I guess. People dont use those harder drugs to explore their mind, or to gain any insight from them. They are used to make you feel happier than normal, and once that is experienced, feeling normal becomes like feeling unhappy and the viscious cycle begins. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uimpirius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Impirius</A> at: 4/18/02 2:32:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=farvel>Farvel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 2:36:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7275.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DARE admits &quot;possible&quot; flaw in strategy.</span><hr size=1> When I was in 5th grade, our parents has to sign a permission slip beofre we could watch a film called &quot;Dead is Dead&quot;. It was a film that showed the nasty effects of cocaine, crack, heroin, PCP, and other very hard drugs. It was VERY graphic,but it made an impression. I decided from that point on that I wouldn't touch any of those drugs. Of course, the film didn't include caffeine, nicotine, alcohol, lsd, or MDMA, which I tried at one time or another(clean since 1998,though). <br>
<br>
A film that I saw when I was 11 was shocking enough to convince me that I would never inject/snort anything. That's more powerful than the DARE program ever was.  <p>Farvel MacDermott<br>
Dark Elf Rogue of the 23rd season<br>
E'ci<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphreshprince.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phresh Prince</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 2:37:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7275.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rpi.edu/~mcguij2/jthm/images/nny-small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DARE admits &quot;possible&quot; flaw in strategy.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Marijuana wont make you pawn everything you own and make you repeatedly jab needles in your veins.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Heroin/coke won't either.  people do it to themselves.  sure it may be a little easier to slip into habitual use, but that doesn't make them the devil.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It wont make you lie on the floor in the fetal position while having seizures and vomiting, hoping for death.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Neither will heroin/coke unless you're a complete and utter @#%$ and can't figure out how to dose correctly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Plus, marijuana isnt likely to make your heart explode or stop your breathing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, it isn't likely too, yet neither is heroin unless you dose way the hell more than you should.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I have seen a whole lot of people start using coke and heroin thinking they can use it responsibly (what an oxymoron) and only do it every now and then. Not one of them was able to control it like they thought they could. Everyone thinks they are the exception to the rule because I damn sure did. Heh, live and learn I guess. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just cuz the vast majority of people can't controll their own actions doesn't mean it isn't possible.<br>
&lt;--living proof!  Its all about self control and moderation.  Sure, you want to bang just one more fix, but its not that hard not to.  Its just like sex... sure it feels good and you want to do it again, that doesn't mean everyone who's dating/married has mad sex every moment they're together.  lol<br>
<br>
Notice in all of my arguments for these drugs I said that one needed to be careful and &quot;knowledgable&quot; with the drug they're using in order to make it possible.  By that I don't mean &quot;i know about heroin.  i can load a rig with the best of them&quot;.  I mean really know the drug.  What is it doing in your brain?  with roughly what amount is physical dependance going to start becoming an issue?  things like that.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I don't know why I continue to argue this topic here, its obviously quite the futile discussion on my part.  /sigh.<br>
<br>
I never said &quot;heroin is safe&quot;  I said even hard drugs can be used quite safely with the right knowledge and understanding of the substance.  You can not refute that.<br>
